= Test 1: Load ggplot2

```{r}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
library(ggplot2)
print("ggplot2 loaded successfully")
```

= Test 2: Create simple plot

```{r}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
gg <- ggplot(iris, aes(x = Sepal.Length, y = Sepal.Width)) +
  geom_point()

typst(gg)
```

= Test 3: Verify ggplot2 is still loaded

```{r}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
print(paste("ggplot2 version:", packageVersion("ggplot2")))
```
